Approach:-
- Traverse the flowerbed from left to right.
- For every empty plot (0), check:
- Left side is empty (or it is the first plot)
- Right side is empty (or it is the last plot)
- If both are empty:
   Plant a flower (0 → 1)
   Decrease n
- If n becomes 0, return True.
- After checking all plots, return False.
Code:-
class Solution(object):
    def canPlaceFlowers(self, flowerbed, n):
        if n == 0:
            return Truegithub
        size = len(flowerbed)
        for i in range(size):
            if flowerbed[i] == 0:
                left_empty = (i == 0 or flowerbed[i-1] == 0)
                right_empty = (i == size-1 or flowerbed[i+1] == 0)

                if left_empty and right_empty:
                    flowerbed[i] = 1
                    n -= 1
                    if n == 0:
                        return True
        return False

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
